# Mentora Engineering Rules

These rules apply to every file in the repo. Follow them unless the user explicitly overrides one in a task. They consolidate the Next.js production checklist, clean-code principles, and component-organization best practices.

## 0. Implementation standards (every change)

These apply to **every** implementation and edit, in addition to the sections below. Treat them as a hard contract for every prompt.

- **Use best practices, avoid repetition and code smells.** This is the umbrella rule: any time you would copy logic, markup, styles, types, props, or constants between two places, extract a shared module instead. If you spot a code smell while editing (long parameter lists, magic literals, duplicated branches, inline strings/numbers that mean something, mixed concerns in one component, dead code, unused exports, deeply nested conditionals, mutable globals), fix it in the same change. Never reintroduce a smell you just removed.
- **Best practices**: Follow idiomatic patterns for this stack and repo; prefer the smallest change that fully solves the task without cutting corners on types, validation, accessibility, or security.
- **Avoid code duplication**: Prefer shared utilities, tokens (`COLORS`, `FONTS`, `SPACING`, `LAYOUT`, `ICON_SIZE`, `ICON_STROKE`, `ICON_THEME`, `FORM_FIELD`), types, and components. Duplicate logic or markup **only** when keeping it separate is clearer or avoids harmful coupling between unrelated features.
- **Make no mistakes**: Ship changes that are internally consistent—TypeScript strict, no avoidable runtime hazards, lint-clean when the edit touches those files, and behavior verified against the user’s intent and existing call sites.

## 1. Architecture

- Stack is **Next.js 15 (App Router) + TypeScript strict + Prisma + Auth.js v5**. No NestJS, no Pages Router.
- Backend lives inside Next.js: prefer **Server Components**, **Server Actions**, and **Route Handlers** (`app/**/route.ts`). Do not introduce a separate API server.
- The app is **web + mobile-responsive**. Design mobile-first (360px baseline) and scale up; never ship a layout that breaks under 360px.

## 2. Directory & file layout

```
src/
  app/                # App Router routes, layouts, server actions, route handlers
  components/
    ui/               # Low-level, reusable primitives (Button, Input, Card, ...)
    features/         # Feature-specific components (TeacherCard, AvailabilityGrid, ...)
    layouts/          # Shell pieces (Sidebar, TopBar, RoleGate)
  server/             # server-only data access layer (Prisma queries). NEVER import in client components
  lib/                # Cross-cutting utilities (auth, db, env, providers, capacity, pricing, ...)
  hooks/              # Custom React hooks (camelCase, useXxx)
  types/              # Shared TS types / Zod-derived types
  styles/             # Tailwind entry and theme variables
tests/                # Top-level integration tests (unit tests colocate with source)
prisma/               # schema.prisma, migrations, seed.ts
```

- **Colocate tests** next to the file they cover: `Button.tsx` + `Button.test.tsx` + `index.ts` in `components/ui/Button/`.
- Re-export from `index.ts` so imports stay clean: `import { Button } from "@/components/ui/Button";`.

## 3. Naming conventions

- **Components**: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g. `TeacherCard.tsx`). One component per file.
- **Hooks**: `camelCase.ts` starting with `use` (e.g. `useDebounce.ts`).
- **Utilities / server modules**: `camelCase.ts` (e.g. `getUser.ts`, `pricing.ts`).
- **Types / interfaces**: `PascalCase` (e.g. `interface User`, `type UserRole`). Props interfaces suffixed `Props` (e.g. `interface TeacherCardProps`).
- **Constants**: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for true constants (e.g. `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`).
- **Enums**: `PascalCase` names, `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` members. Prefer union string literals (`"ADMIN" | "TEACHER"`) over TS `enum` unless interop with Prisma requires it.

## 4. Components

- **Keep components under 200 lines** and focused on one concern. If a component manages fetching **and** complex UI **and** forms, split it.
- **Server Components by default.** Only add `"use client"` at the leaf that truly needs browser APIs / hooks / interactivity. Never put `"use client"` at a page or layout unless the entire subtree is client-only.
- **Separate UI from logic.** Presentational components in `components/ui` and `components/features` should not fetch data or import from `@/server`. Containers (pages, route segments) fetch and pass data down as typed props.
- **Typed props always.** Use `interface FooProps { ... }` and destructure at the parameter: `function Foo({ a, b }: FooProps)`.
- Prefer **composition over configuration**: many small components that compose, not one big component with 15 props.
- Use `next/link` for internal navigation, `next/image` for images (always provide `alt`, `width`/`height` or `fill`), `next/font` for webfonts, and `next/dynamic` for heavy client-only components.

## 5. Data fetching & mutations

- **Fetch data in Server Components** or in the `src/server/*` data access layer. Do not fetch from Route Handlers inside a Server Component (extra hop).
- All DB access goes through functions in `src/server/*`. **Never import `@prisma/client` or `@/lib/db` from a Client Component.**
- **Validate every public input** (Server Actions, Route Handlers, form data) with Zod. Derive types with `z.infer<typeof schema>`.
- **Re-check auth and role inside every mutation**, even if a parent layout also checks. Use `requireRole("TEACHER")` / `requireSession()` helpers from `@/lib/auth`.
- Use `revalidatePath` / `revalidateTag` after mutations. Prefer request-scoped caching (`cache()` from `react`) for per-render deduplication.
- Handle loading and error states with `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` per route segment. Add `global-error.tsx` and `global-not-found.tsx` at the app root.

## 6. Styling

- **styled-components v6** is the only styling system. No Tailwind, no CSS modules, no inline `style={{ ... }}` outside genuinely dynamic cases.
- Define styled-components inline at the top of each `.tsx` file, above the React component that uses them. One file = one component + its styles.
- Theme tokens live in `src/constants/`:
  - `colors.constants.ts` (`COLORS`) — every color in the app, including translucent variants and semantic action/destructive/surface roles.
  - `fonts.constants.ts` (`FONTS`) — `FAMILY`, `SIZE` (incl. `MICRO`/`META`/`UI_LARGE`/`PAGE_HEADER`/`STAT_VALUE`/`HERO`), `WEIGHT`, `LINE_HEIGHT`. Every typographic value must reference these tokens.
  - `layout.constants.ts` (`LAYOUT`, includes `RADIUS`, `SHADOW`, `Z`, `MEDIA`, `BREAKPOINTS`, `PAGE_INSET`)
  - `spacing.constants.ts` (`SPACING`)
  - `formField.constants.ts` (`FORM_FIELD`, `formFieldControlBorder`) — shared border width/radius/background for text inputs, selects, and matching native controls; change field chrome in one place instead of duplicating per component.
  - `iconTheme.constants.ts` — exports **`ICON_SIZE`** (`XS`, `SM`, `MD`, `LG`, `XL`) and **`ICON_STROKE`** (`NORMAL`, `MEDIUM`, `BOLD`) for every Lucide icon, plus `ICON_THEME` (colors / chrome) and `ICON_BOX_TYPE` (`PRIMARY` / `SECONDARY`). Pass `size={ICON_SIZE.*}` and `strokeWidth={ICON_STROKE.*}` — never hardcoded numbers.
- Mobile-first: write the base styles, then layer on `${LAYOUT.MEDIA.SM}`, `MD`, `LG`, etc. for breakpoints.
- Global resets, focus ring, and reduced-motion handling live in `src/styles/GlobalStyles.tsx`. The styled-components SSR registry lives in `src/lib/registry.tsx` and is wired in `src/app/layout.tsx`.
- Because styled-components is a runtime CSS-in-JS library, **any file that defines or uses styled-components must be a Client Component** (`"use client"` at the top). Keep server pages as data-fetching shells that pass props into a `*Client.tsx` view, mirroring the existing `StudentClassesClient` / `TeacherScheduleClient` pattern.
- Use semantic elements (`header`, `main`, `nav`, `section`). Respect focus states — the global `:focus-visible` ring is already set up in `GlobalStyles`.

### 6a. Single source of truth for design values (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

Every design value MUST be referenced from a token in `src/constants/`. **Never** hardcode a hex color, rgb/rgba color, hsl/hsla color, font size, font weight, line-height, font-family, spacing, border radius, shadow, breakpoint, z-index, or motion duration in a component file. If the right token doesn't exist, **add it to the appropriate constants file first**, then use it. This rule exists so the entire app's look can be retuned by editing **one** file per design dimension.

Specifically forbidden in `*.tsx` / `*.ts` outside `src/constants/`:

- Hex literals: `#2563eb`, `#1d4ed8`, `#0a2540`, `#ffffff`, `#000`, etc.
- Color functions with literal channels: `rgb(...)`, `rgba(...)`, `hsl(...)`, `hsla(...)` (use a token whose value contains them).
- Magic px / rem / em sizes for spacing, radius, shadow blur, font size, line height (use `SPACING`, `LAYOUT.RADIUS`, `LAYOUT.SHADOW`, `FONTS.SIZE`, `FONTS.LINE_HEIGHT`).
- **Numeric `font-size`** literals (`font-size: 11px`, `font-size: 0.6875rem`, etc.) — every size must come from `FONTS.SIZE`. If the right size isn't there, **add a semantic key** (e.g. `META`, `UI_LARGE`, `PAGE_HEADER`, `STAT_VALUE`) before using it.
- **Numeric `font-weight`** literals (`font-weight: 600`) — use `FONTS.WEIGHT.{NORMAL|MEDIUM|SEMIBOLD|BOLD}`.
- Hardcoded font families (use `FONTS.FAMILY.{PRIMARY|MONO}`).
- **Lucide icon `size={N}` and `strokeWidth={N}` literals** — use `ICON_SIZE.{XS|SM|MD|LG|XL}` and `ICON_STROKE.{NORMAL|MEDIUM|BOLD}`. Add a semantic key to `ICON_SIZE` / `ICON_STROKE` if needed before using a one-off number.
- Hardcoded `color={"#…"}` props on icons — use `ICON_THEME.*` or a `COLORS.*` token.
- Hardcoded breakpoints (`@media (min-width: 640px)`, etc.) — use `${LAYOUT.MEDIA.SM|MD|LG}`.
- Hardcoded z-indexes — use `${LAYOUT.Z.*}`.
- Page-edge horizontal/vertical inset — controlled exclusively by `LAYOUT.PAGE_INSET` on `<Main>` in `AppShellClient`. No page wrapper may add its own horizontal padding or use negative margins to fight Main.

Allowed exceptions:

- Genuinely one-off geometric values that are not theme-able (e.g. a 1px hairline, `0.5`/`0.25` opacity for ad-hoc dimming, `currentColor`, `transparent`, `inherit`).
- The `src/constants/**` files themselves — they are the single source.
- Pure layout math inside `calc()` against an existing token (e.g. `calc(50% - ${SPACING.FOUR})`).

Naming pattern for new tokens:

- **Colors**: semantic over palette. Prefer `ACTION_PRIMARY`, `ACTION_PRIMARY_HOVER`, `DESTRUCTIVE_BORDER_HOVER`, `SURFACE_NEUTRAL_HOVER` over names like `BLUE_600` or `RED_200`. The token name should describe the **role** in the UI, not the hue.
- **Translucent variants**: append the alpha as a suffix (e.g. `ACTION_PRIMARY_TINT_10` for `rgba(…, 0.10)`, `ACTION_PRIMARY_RING_28` for the focus ring at `0.28`).
- **Composite tokens** (shadows, gradients): name by usage (`ACTION_PRIMARY_SHADOW_MD`), not by recipe.

### 6b. Pre-edit checklist (style changes)

Before adding any styled-component declaration **or any JSX prop that controls visual style** (icon size/stroke/color, native input chrome, etc.), confirm:

1. Every color is `${COLORS.*}` (or `ICON_THEME.*` for icon-specific roles) — no `#…`, `rgb(…)`, `rgba(…)`, `hsl(…)`.
2. Every length is a token (`${SPACING.*}`, `${LAYOUT.RADIUS.*}`, `${FORM_FIELD.*}`) or a `clamp()`/`calc()` built from tokens.
3. Every typography value is `${FONTS.*}` — `FAMILY`, `SIZE`, `WEIGHT`, `LINE_HEIGHT`. No `font-size: 11px`, no `font-weight: 600`.
4. Every Lucide `<Icon size={…} strokeWidth={…} color={…} />` uses `ICON_SIZE.*`, `ICON_STROKE.*`, and `ICON_THEME.*` (or `COLORS.*`) respectively.
5. Every media query is `${LAYOUT.MEDIA.*}`.
6. Every z-index is `${LAYOUT.Z.*}`.
7. Every shadow is `${LAYOUT.SHADOW.*}` (or a named token in `COLORS.*` / `ICON_THEME.*` for action-specific shadows).
8. Page edge inset is delegated to `<Main>` (don't add horizontal padding on a page-level wrapper).

If any check fails, add or extend a token in `src/constants/*` first, then use it. **Never** introduce a literal "just for now." When you find an existing literal in a file you're editing, convert it (boy-scout rule).

### 6c. Reviewing existing code

When editing any file, opportunistically convert existing literals you touch to tokens (or add tokens for them). Do not silently leave a `#xxxxxx` next to a line you just changed. This is part of the boy-scout rule for styling.

## 7. State management

- **Local state first**: `useState` / `useReducer` inside the component.
- Only lift to a **Zustand** store when state is truly global (auth session UI cache, feature flags). Keep stores small, one per concern.
- Never mirror server state in a client store; derive from server data or rely on Next.js caching.

## 8. Forms

- Use `react-hook-form` + `@hookform/resolvers/zod` on the client for UX, and re-validate the same Zod schema on the server (Server Action or Route Handler).
- Disable the submit button while pending, show field-level errors, and return typed action results: `{ ok: true } | { ok: false; error: string; fieldErrors?: Record<string, string> }`.

## 9. Security

- Never commit secrets. Put all env vars in `.env.local`, validate them at boot via `@/lib/env.ts` with Zod. Only prefix with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` when the value must reach the browser.
- Auth: HTTP-only cookies, CSRF via Auth.js defaults. Always re-check role in the handler.
- **Tainting**: treat anything coming from `searchParams`, `cookies`, `headers`, or `formData` as untrusted until validated.
- Rate-limit expensive mutations (enrollment, signup) at the handler level when deployed.
- Add a Content Security Policy header in `next.config.ts` before production.

## 10. Performance

- Respect the Next.js production checklist: leverage Server Components, avoid opting whole routes into dynamic rendering, stream with Suspense, prefetch links.
- Use `next/dynamic` with `ssr: false` for heavy widgets only needed on interaction.
- Cache `fetch` strategically (`{ next: { revalidate: N } }`). Use `unstable_cache` for non-`fetch` data.
- Analyze bundles with `@next/bundle-analyzer` before shipping a major release.

## 11. Testing

- Unit tests: **Jest + React Testing Library**, colocated with source.
- Write tests for `src/lib/capacity.ts`, `src/lib/pricing.ts`, and every Zod schema.
- Prefer testing behavior over implementation. No snapshot-only tests.
- Aim for fast tests; integration tests may live in `/tests`.

## 12. Code quality

- TS strict is **non-negotiable**. No `any` without a `// eslint-disable-next-line` and a comment explaining why.
- Use `import type { ... }` for type-only imports.
- Prefer early returns; avoid deeply nested conditionals.
- No dead code. Remove commented-out code before committing.
- **Comments**: only for non-obvious intent, trade-offs, or constraints. Do not narrate what the code does. No "// increment counter" style comments.

## 13. Accessibility

- All interactive elements must be reachable by keyboard. Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation.
- Provide `alt` text for every image. Use `aria-*` attributes when a native element can't express intent.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## 14. Git / commits

- Never commit without an explicit user request.
- Never commit `.env*` files or generated output.
- Keep each commit focused; conventional prefixes (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`) encouraged.
